{
  "local_port": 50454,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best date cake recipes?",
  "response": "Here are three delicious date cake recipes, each offering a unique twist on this classic treat:\n\n### 1. Classic Date Cake\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup chopped dates (pitted)\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1 cup boiling water\n- 1 cup sugar\n- 1/2 cup unsalted butter, softened\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 \u00bd cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 cup chopped walnuts or pecans (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease and flour a 9-inch round or square cake pan.\n2. In a small bowl, combine the chopped dates and baking soda. Pour boiling water over the mixture and let it sit for about 10 minutes.\n3. In a large mixing bowl, cream together the sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add the eggs one at a time, followed by the vanilla extract.\n4. In another bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, and salt.\n5. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture, alternating with the date mixture. Mix until just combined.\n6. Fold in the nuts if using. Pour the batter into the prepared pan.\n7. Bake for 30-35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n8. Let it cool in the pan for 10 minutes before transferring it to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n### 2. Sticky Date Cake with Toffee Sauce\n\n**Ingredients for the Cake:**\n- 1 1/2 cups chopped dates (pitted)\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1 cup boiling water\n- 1/2 cup unsalted butter, softened\n- 1 cup brown sugar\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n\n**Ingredients for the Toffee Sauce:**\n- 1 cup brown sugar\n- 1/2 cup heavy cream\n- 1/4 cup unsalted butter\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) and grease a 9-inch round cake pan.\n2. Mix dates and baking soda in a bowl. Pour boiling water over the dates and let sit for 10 minutes. Mash slightly with a fork.\n3. Cream butter and brown sugar together in a large bowl. Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.\n4. In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, and salt. Gradually add to the butter mixture, alternating with the date mixture.\n5. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 30-35 minutes.\n6. While the cake is baking, prepare the toffee sauce. In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, cream, butter, and vanilla. Bring to a simmer and cook for about 5 minutes until thickened.\n7. Once the cake is done, allow it to cool for 10 minutes before removing it from the pan. Serve warm with the toffee sauce drizzled on top.\n\n### 3. Date and Almond Flour Cake (Gluten-Free)\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup pitted dates, chopped\n- 1 cup boiling water\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- 2 cups almond flour\n- 1/2 cup maple syrup or honey\n- 1/4 cup coconut oil, melted\n- 3 large eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 teaspoon cinnamon\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 cup chopped almonds (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat the oven to 325\u00b0F (160\u00b0C). Grease a 9-inch round cake pan.\n2. In a bowl, combine the chopped dates and baking soda. Pour boiling water over the dates and let them sit for 10 minutes.\n3. In another bowl, mix almond flour, cinnamon, and salt.\n4. In a mixing bowl, whisk together the maple syrup (or honey), melted coconut oil, eggs, and vanilla extract. Stir in the date mixture.\n5. Gradually mix in the dry ingredients until well combined. Fold in the chopped almonds if desired.\n6. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.\n7. Allow to cool before slicing and serving.\n\nThese recipes highlight the natural sweetness of dates and can be enjoyed on their own or with your favorite toppings! Enjoy baking!",
